            <title>Ludeca Unveils New Sensor System for Machinery Alignment</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;img alt="" src="http://media.noria.com/sites/Uploads/2012/10/30/ad949132-0305-4a73-afa1-2c3b52d154a6_Ludeca_Sensalign-Sensors.jpeg" style="margin: 7px; width: 300px; height: 235px; float: left;" /&gt;Ludeca recently launched a new intelligent sensor system for machinery alignment. SensAlign combines patented sensor technology into the Rotalign Ultra iS platform to yield instantaneous data acquisition and real-time results with guaranteed 100-percent accuracy under even the roughest of field conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The SensAlign intelligence automatically considers the effects of ambient vibration, acceleration of rotation, backlash, speed of rotation and other factors in determining the quality factor (QF) of alignment readings. This makes the system ideal for long-term stand-alone monitoring of machine positional change as well as routine everyday shaft alignment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	An improved user-friendly interface enables the Rotalign Ultra iS to be faster while still collecting thousands of measurement points with its patented Continuous IntelliSweep method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Alignment results can be achieved with the Rotalign Ultra iS in three easy steps: enter dimensions, measure and view results. The accurate alignments can reduce unwanted maintenance costs, power consumption and vibration levels while increasing equipment availability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.ludeca.com/"&gt;www.ludeca.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/alignment_and_balancing/~4/gTHBH-Q08yY" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
